Substitute each point into $y =  rac{8}{7}x - 14$:<ul><li><strong>A)</strong> $(0,  rac{8}{7})$: $y = 0 - 14 = -14 
eq  rac{8}{7}$ ✗</li><li><strong>B)</strong> $(6, 9)$: $y =  rac{48}{7} - 14 =  rac{-50}{7} 
eq 9$ ✗</li><li><strong>C)</strong> $(14, 2)$: $y =  rac{112}{7} - 14 = 16 - 14 = 2$ ✓</li><li><strong>D)</strong> $(15, 1)$: $y =  rac{120}{7} - 14 =  rac{22}{7} 
eq 1$ ✗</li></ul>Point $(14, 2)$ satisfies the line equation. That matches choice C — <strong>C</strong> is correct.
